    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "The model is valid within the following bounded operating conditions: axial compressive load 0–2500 N applied at displacement-controlled rate 25 ± 2 mm/min; bending moment arm 50 ± 1 mm per ASTM F1717 fixture geometry; screw outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm (nominal 7.5 mm, manufacturing tolerance ±0.1 mm); screw length 40–55 mm; titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V ELI with elastic modulus 110 ± 5 GPa and yield strength 880 ± 30 MPa; UHMWPE block density 0.93–0.95 g/cm³; ambient temperature 20–25 °C; test medium air (dry). Validation experiments sampled boundary points at 0 N and 2400 N axial load, screw lengths 40 mm and 55 mm, and both laboratories confirmed material properties within stated ranges."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability constraint: non-cannulated Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 static loading only",
      "description": "This credibility assessment applies exclusively to non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs manufactured from Ti-6Al-4V ELI with outer diameter 7.3–7.7 mm under quasi-static ASTM F1717 compression-bending. It does not extend to cannulated screw designs, dynamic fatigue loading, cortical or cancellous bone simulants other than UHMWPE blocks per F1717, screw diameters outside 7.3–7.7 mm, or alloys other than Ti-6Al-4V ELI. Clinical in vivo loading conditions are outside scope."
    }
  },
